related_questions.question: Do staples still have stores?
related_questions.snippet: The US owner of Staples has sold the UK arm, which employs 1,100 people across 106 stores, to Hilco for a "nominal" sum. Hilco said it was planning to phase out Staples-branded shops over the coming months. Staples also has online and business-to-business operations.Nov 17, 2016

related_questions.question: What is Staples called now?
related_questions.snippet: While there has been no official announcement from Hilco on the name change or exactly how many stores will remain open, a rebrand to the new name of Office Outlet has begun. This follows the change of the official name of the company in early January from Staples Retail UK to SUK Retail.Feb 27, 2017
